Package project3

Class Interpreter

java.lang.Object
project3.Interpreter
public class Interpreter
extends java.lang.Object
This class create a canvas and handle the input string into each command to draw shapes.

    • checkCommand

      private void checkCommand​(Canvas canvas)
      This method uses method readword() to check the word is a command or variable. If the word is a command, it will execute the command on the input canvas. If the word is a variable, it will look for "=" sign and add the values in the bracket to the environment ass a new shape
      Parameters:
      canvas - A canvas used to show the contents

    • skipWhiteSpace

      Method to skip over any space or end line at the current position of the input

    • readWord

      private java.lang.String readWord()
      Read a word from input. It can be a variable name or command If the word is a variable name, it must starts with a letter
      Returns:
      A substring which contains a command or a variable name

    • match

      private void match​(java.lang.String text)
      Match a string of text which is expected at the current input position. If the match fails, then an error is produced.
      Parameters:
      text - The string that need to be matched

    • checkBracketExpression

      private Shape checkBracketExpression()
      Evaluate a shape expression at the current position of the input string. This is done by first looking at the current character in the input string. If the first character of the input string is a '(', then it signals the start of a bracketed expression. If the first character of the input string is a '[', then we read the rectangle.
      Returns:
      A shape constructed from the evaluated result

    • checkParenthesis

      private Shape checkParenthesis()
      Evaluate a bracketed shape expression.
      Returns:
      A shape constructed from the evaluated result

    • readShape

      private Shape readShape()
      Evaluate a rectangle expression, which is four numbers separated by comma's and '[', ']'
      Returns:
      A rectangle constructed from the evaluated result

    • readNumber

      private int readNumber()
      Read a number at the current input position
      Returns:
      The integer number parsed from current input position

    • readVariable

      private Shape readVariable()
      Evaluate a variable expression at the current input position. When the variable name is determined, its current value is looked up in the environment.
      Returns:
      A shape constructed from the evaluated result

    • readColor

      private Color readColor()
      Read a color at the current input position. A color is a string of Hex color code
      Returns:
      A color parsed from current input position
